- Added test `execute_personAddedWithLesson_correctlyPopulatesLessonSet`
to ensure lessons are correctly populated into the lesson set when a
person is added.
- Added test `execute_duplicateLesson_throwsCommandException` to handle
cases where duplicate lesson times are detected when adding or
editing a person.
- Added test
`constructor_startTimeAfterEndTime_throwsIllegalArgumentException` to
validate that lessons with invalid time ranges (start time after end
time) are not allowed.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add feature to reject clashing lessons
commitResults.messageBody:
Only lessons with 1:1 mapping ie same day and time are detected and
rejected

Lets,
- Detect and reject lessons that overlap on the same day
- Lessons are considered clashing if
any part of the lesson overlaps with another on the same day.

Notes:
- Lessons can be back to back.
- E.g A lesson from 1900-2000 and another from 2000-2100 is allowed

commitResults.messageTitle: Bug Fix: Resolved clash detection issue & implemented hashCode()
commitResults.messageBody:
Bug in `isClashingWithOtherLesson()` where lessons on
different days but with the same time were incorrectly flagged as
clashing.

`hashCode()` not overridden in `Lesson`. Result in incorrect behaviour
when checking equality of `Set<Lesson>`

Lets,
- Accounts for both day and time when checking for lesson clashes.
- Implement `hashCode()` in the `Lesson` class to ensure consistent
behaviour when using hash-based collections (e.g., `HashSet`).
This resolves issues where lessons with the same day, start time, and
end time were treated as different objects.

commitResults.messageBody:
- Added functionality to display detailed information when a new lesson
clashes with an existing one.

exact lesson details of the conflict.
- Improves user experience by making it easier to resolve scheduling
conflicts through clearer information on the source of each clash.
- Typo in puml file name
- Change unit test to match new implementation of clash detection

Add method to retrieve a student's next lesson
commitResults.messageBody:
- Implemented a method to find and return the next scheduled lesson for
a student based on the current date and time.
- The method identifies the lesson with the shortest time until its
start, allowing for better scheduling insights.
- Returns null if no upcoming lessons are scheduled.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor student lesson storage from Set to List
commitResults.messageBody:
- Changed the data structure for storing lessons from a Set to a List to
enable easy indexing.
- This change allows for efficient addition, deletion, and access of
lessons based on position.
- Updated related methods to accommodate the List structure.

commitResults.messageBody:
Student can be allocated two or more lessons that clash

Lets,
- Resolved the issue where user could add overlapping lessons when
adding students
- Issue exist because the system only checked for clashes with
pre-existing lessons and did not account for lessons added
simultaneously with conflicting schedules.
